                            <comment id="16554019" author="githubbot" created="Tue, 24 Jul 2018 09:49:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user twalthr opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/6403&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/6403&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-9934&quot; title=&quot;Kafka table source factory produces invalid field mapping&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-9934&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-9934&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;table&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Fix invalid field mapping by Kafka table source factory&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;ol&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;What is the purpose of the change&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ol&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;    According to the `DefinedFieldMapping` interface the field mapping can also contain the input fields. However, the Kafka table source factory was calling `SchemaValidator#deriveFieldMapping` with its own schema instead of the the input type. &lt;/p&gt;


&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;ol&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Brief change log&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ol&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Replace schema with type in `SchemaValidator#deriveFieldMapping` to avoid confusion&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Adapted tests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;ol&gt;
